    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Obama's Narrator</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Steven A Ludsin letter comments on April 1 article on David Axelrod, media and political consultant to Barack Obama</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Ben Wallace-Wells's article (April 1) was informative. Senator Obama comes across as a fresh face, and David Axelrod seems to have guided him well. The roughness of the political game was reflected in the story of Senator Clinton's important work for children like David Axelrod's son -- work that, Axelrod's wife, Susan, said, was ''one of the most important things anyone has done for epilepsy.'' And yet David Axelrod is now ''dedicated to derailing this woman's career.''</p>
      </block>
